The paper presents a method for motion planning for robots with hybrid locomotion, which is a topic within the field of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves combining graph search and trajectory optimization, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic optimization, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
